entry.def: A subdivision is an area, part, or section of something which is itself a part of something larger.

example.ex: Months are a conventional subdivision of the year.
example.tran: 通常可将一年再按月细分。

entry.tran: 分割成的小块土地(供开发住房)
entry.def: A subdivision is an area of land for building houses on.

example.ex: Rammick lives high on a ridge in a 400-home subdivision.
example.tran: 拉米克住在高耸的山脊上一片有 400 户人家的地方。

means.word_mean: 1. an area composed of subdivided lots
2. the act of subdividing; division of something previously divided
3. an administrative division of some larger or more complex organization;
4. a self-contained part of a larger composition (written or musical);

sentences.sentence: "he always turns first to the business section"
"the history of this work is discussed in the next section"

means.word_mean: 5. a section of a section; a part of a part; i.e., a part of something already divided

Sentence.sentence: Last September the couple moved into a 1,500-square-foot home in Premier Gardens, a subdivision of 95 "zero-energy homes"(ZEH) just outside town.
Premier Gardens is one of a half-dozen subdivisions in California where every home cuts power consumption by 50%, mostly by using low-power appliances and solar panels.
